author: Henry Belot
title: Live: Energy on agenda as politicians face off in Question Time
text:
By Laura Brierley Newton and Jason Di Rosso for The Final Cut 
An obsession with Catholicism is a main theme in Martin Scorsese's latest film, as he continues a search for "the spiritual human condition". 
That includes the barista who gets your name wrong every time and the neighbour who brings in your bin every week. Top Stories
